The '''Apple Magic Mouse''' is a [[multi-touch]] [[Mouse (computing)|mouse]] manufactured and sold by [[Apple Inc.]] It was announced and sold for the first time on [[October 20]], [[2009]].<ref name="Engadget-announcement">{{cite web|url=http://www.engadget.com/2009/10/20/apples-magic-mouse-multitouch-gestures-bluetooth-four-month/|title=Apple's Magic Mouse: one button, multitouch gestures, Bluetooth, four-month battery life|last=Topolsky|first=Joshua|date=2009-10-20|publisher=[[Engadget]]|accessdate=2009-10-25}}</ref> The Apple Magic Mouse is the first consumer mouse to have [[multi-touch]] capabilities.{{Citation needed|date=October 2009}} Taking after the [[iPhone]], [[iPod Touch]], and multi-touch [[trackpad]]s, the Magic Mouse provides a new way to interact with desktop computers using [[gesture recognition|gestures]] such as swiping and scrolling.

The mouse requires [[Mac OS X v10.5|Mac OS X 10.5.8]] and [[Bluetooth]]. It can be configured as a left-handed or right-handed mouse and uses [[Mouse (computing)#Laser mice|laser tracking]] for increased pointer accuracy over previous generation Apple mice.<ref name="Apple store">{{cite web|url=http://store.apple.com/us/product/MB829LL/A|title=Apple Magic Mouse|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=2009-10-25}}</ref> Since its release, it has been included along with a wireless keyboard with the [[iMac]].

Initial reception to the Magic Mouse has been mixed, with positive reactions to its scrolling functions<ref name="Gizmodo-review">{{cite web|url=http://gizmodo.com/5386202/apple-magic-mouse-review|title=Apple Magic Mouse Review|last=Chen|first=Jason|date=2009-10-21|publisher=[[Gizmodo]]|accessdate=2009-10-25}}</ref> but negative reactions to its inability to [[Middle click#Common mouse operations|middle click]], or trigger [[Expos<U+00E9> (Mac OS X)|Expos<U+00E9>]], [[Dashboard_(software)|Dashboard]] or [[Spaces (software)|Spaces]] (features offered by its [[Apple_Mighty_Mouse|predecessor]]).<ref name="Macworld-review">{{cite web|url=http://www.macworld.com/article/143410/2009/10/magic_mouse.html|title=First Look: Apple Magic Mouse|last=Loyola|first=Roman|date=2009-10-21|publisher=[[Macworld]]|accessdate=2009-10-25}}</ref> It has also been criticized for long-term [[ergonomic]] concerns.<ref name="I4U-review">{{cite web|url=http://www.i4u.com/article27784.html|title=Magic Mouse Reviews Raise Ergonomic Issues|last=Lugmayr|first=Luigi|date=2009-10-21|publisher=I4U|accessdate=2009-10-25}}</ref>

